00:39:58,080 --> 00:40:00,020
 forced to wear a crown of thorns,

839
00:40:00,020 --> 00:40:02,280
 paraded through the city

840
00:40:02,280 --> 00:40:06,780
 for nothing of his wrongdoing of his own,

841
00:40:06,780 --> 00:40:11,120
 but because he went to take yours and my sin.

842
00:40:11,120 --> 00:40:13,320
 You think Jesus doesn't understand betrayal?

843
00:40:13,320 --> 00:40:17,860
 You think Jesus doesn't understand pain and suffering?

844
00:40:17,860 --> 00:40:21,820
 He absolutely understands it.

845
00:40:21,820 --> 00:40:29,080
 Luke 23, "And when they came to the place

846
00:40:29,080 --> 00:40:31,800
 "that's called Skull, there they crucified him,"

847
00:40:31,800 --> 00:40:34,000
 being Jesus, "with the criminals."

848
00:40:34,000 --> 00:40:37,560
 They treated him, our Savior, as a criminal

849
00:40:37,560 --> 00:40:40,680
 because of my sin.

850
00:40:40,680 --> 00:40:43,840
 And they hung him there,

851
00:40:43,840 --> 00:40:49,000
 bleeding, alone.

852
00:40:49,000 --> 00:40:53,000
 And what does he say?

853
00:40:53,000 --> 00:40:57,160
 He said, "Father, forgive them,

854
00:40:57,160 --> 00:40:58,800
 "for they know not what they do."

855
00:40:59,640 --> 00:41:01,840
 (chuckles)

856
00:41:01,840 --> 00:41:06,840
 Our Savior, in the midst of being betrayed

857
00:41:06,840 --> 00:41:09,560
 by the very people he came to save,

858
00:41:09,560 --> 00:41:12,160
 he says, "Forgive them."

859
00:41:12,160 --> 00:41:15,580
 This is our God.

860
00:41:15,580 --> 00:41:22,680
 See, forgiveness is the central core aspect of our faith.

861
00:41:22,680 --> 00:41:25,360
 There's no justification.

862
00:41:25,360 --> 00:41:26,400
 There's no sanctification.

863
00:41:26,400 --> 00:41:28,720
 There's no nothing without forgiveness.

864
00:41:28,720 --> 00:41:30,240
 We don't have a faith.

865
00:41:30,240 --> 00:41:33,540
 We don't have a Savior without forgiveness.

866
00:41:33,540 --> 00:41:38,040
 And so the only way we can experience the true fullness

867
00:41:38,040 --> 00:41:41,640
 of what God has for us is that we receive that forgiveness

868
00:41:41,640 --> 00:41:44,040
 and then we extend it to others.

869
00:41:44,040 --> 00:41:47,040
 Because if we don't, who are we to say,

870
00:41:47,040 --> 00:41:49,080
 we receive all that forgiveness, and then we say,

871
00:41:49,080 --> 00:41:52,480
 "No, I'm not gonna forgive others."

872
00:41:52,480 --> 00:41:56,200
 Then we become a block to the love

873
00:41:56,200 --> 00:41:58,760
 and the power of forgiveness in this world

874
00:41:58,760 --> 00:42:00,960
 because we hoard it for ourselves.

875
00:42:00,960 --> 00:42:05,720
 Or we don't think Jesus has the power to forgive,

876
00:42:05,720 --> 00:42:08,560
 which both is not true.

877
00:42:08,560 --> 00:42:11,740
 Is forgiveness easy?

878
00:42:11,740 --> 00:42:13,520
 No, it's absolutely not.

879
00:42:13,520 --> 00:42:17,480
 But thankfully, we have the person of Jesus

880
00:42:17,480 --> 00:42:19,240
 in the presence of the Holy Spirit.

881
00:42:19,240 --> 00:42:24,040
 I'm not gonna tell you what to do.

882
00:42:24,040 --> 00:42:26,180
 I'm going to ask the Holy Spirit to do that.

883
00:42:27,180 --> 00:42:29,140
 I'm gonna share one last story.

884
00:42:29,140 --> 00:42:30,040
 Can I get the pen?

885
00:42:30,040 --> 00:42:35,960
 I grew up in a Chinese family.

886
00:42:35,960 --> 00:42:37,460
 My parents are from Hong Kong.

887
00:42:37,460 --> 00:42:41,280
 And my dad immigrated to the States,

888
00:42:41,280 --> 00:42:42,780
 had a great upbringing there.

889
00:42:42,780 --> 00:42:43,940
 And then we came back to Hong Kong

890
00:42:43,940 --> 00:42:45,780
 and I lived the expat life.

891
00:42:45,780 --> 00:42:46,820
 I went to island school,

892
00:42:46,820 --> 00:42:48,220
 if there's anyone who went to island school.

893
00:42:48,220 --> 00:42:50,940
 I went to, you know, I was able to have all the things,

894
00:42:50,940 --> 00:42:53,540
 you know, tennis club, golf club, woo-hoo.

895
00:42:53,540 --> 00:42:54,500
 I lived the life, right?

896
00:42:54,500 --> 00:42:55,840
 I even went to university in the States.

897
00:42:55,840 --> 00:42:58,820
 So my father being a very Chinese man,

898
00:42:58,820 --> 00:43:01,820
 loved us in the way that Chinese men do.

899
00:43:01,820 --> 00:43:05,700
 He provided for us, right?

900
00:43:05,700 --> 00:43:08,340
 Did I have a relationship with my father?

901
00:43:08,340 --> 00:43:09,380
 No.

902
00:43:09,380 --> 00:43:11,620
 Did I sit down and talk to my dad

903
00:43:11,620 --> 00:43:14,760
 about all my hopes and dreams?

904
00:43:14,760 --> 00:43:15,600
 No.

905
00:43:15,600 --> 00:43:20,080
 Did I sit there and just ask him how his day was?

906
00:43:20,080 --> 00:43:23,040
 No, that's not the relationship that I have with my father.

907
00:43:25,340 --> 00:43:27,080
 In the late stages of his life,

908
00:43:27,080 --> 00:43:28,160
 he had severe dementia

909
00:43:28,160 --> 00:43:30,080
 and a number of other ailments with his body,

910
00:43:30,080 --> 00:43:32,740
 but then he developed a cancer in his jawbone.

911
00:43:32,740 --> 00:43:36,120
 And because his overall health was so poor,

912
00:43:36,120 --> 00:43:38,760
 the doctors said, "We cannot operate on him.

913
00:43:38,760 --> 00:43:40,560
 "He won't survive the operation."

914
00:43:40,560 --> 00:43:42,840
 So essentially they said, "There's nothing we can do."

915
00:43:42,840 --> 00:43:44,720
 So we just tried in the later stages of his life

916
00:43:44,720 --> 00:43:48,360
 to have his quality of life as positive as it could be.

917
00:43:48,360 --> 00:43:51,040
 But the cancer grew to a point

918
00:43:51,040 --> 00:43:53,760
 where it fused his mouth shut.

919
00:43:53,760 --> 00:43:54,780
 So he could no longer chew.

920
00:43:54,780 --> 00:43:57,120
 And if there was one thing that my father loved doing,

921
00:43:57,120 --> 00:43:58,960
 it was eating.

922
00:43:58,960 --> 00:44:01,320
 He was diabetic, but he loved his ice creams

923
00:44:01,320 --> 00:44:03,160
 and he loved fatty char siu.

924
00:44:03,160 --> 00:44:04,680
 It was just ridiculous.

925
00:44:04,680 --> 00:44:07,880
 But once he could no longer take solid food,

926
00:44:07,880 --> 00:44:10,860
 he just disintegrated.

927
00:44:10,860 --> 00:44:14,320
 And so we're very thankful that he didn't suffer very long,

928
00:44:14,320 --> 00:44:16,420
 but ultimately he succumbed to the cancer.

929
00:44:16,420 --> 00:44:18,760
 A few hours after he passed,

930
00:44:18,760 --> 00:44:21,440
 I was outside in the hospital,

931
00:44:21,440 --> 00:44:24,080
 outside the operating room,

932
00:44:24,080 --> 00:44:27,680
 and I was able to go and say my farewell to my father,

933
00:44:27,680 --> 00:44:29,880
 just a few hours passed.

934
00:44:29,880 --> 00:44:30,720
 I stood there

935
00:44:30,720 --> 00:44:37,060
 and I said, "Dad, thank you so much for the life

936
00:44:37,060 --> 00:44:38,400
 "that you provided for me."

937
00:44:38,400 --> 00:44:40,640
 Then I found myself saying,

938
00:44:40,640 --> 00:44:43,500
 "You know, Dad, I forgive you for not being the father

939
00:44:43,500 --> 00:44:44,460
 "I wish you were."

940
00:44:44,460 --> 00:44:48,380
 And I would love to tell you

941
00:44:48,380 --> 00:44:51,760
 that I had this wave of emotion, of tears of joy,

942
00:44:51,760 --> 00:44:54,800
 and this just release, but I didn't.

943
00:44:54,800 --> 00:44:55,840
 You know what I felt?

944
00:44:55,840 --> 00:44:58,020
 Shame.

945
00:44:58,020 --> 00:45:00,680
 I don't have very many regrets in my life,

946
00:45:00,680 --> 00:45:03,520
 but I felt in that moment, shame.

947
00:45:03,520 --> 00:45:09,200
 Because why didn't I care enough

948
00:45:09,200 --> 00:45:12,800
 to say this to my father when he was of sound mind

949
00:45:12,800 --> 00:45:13,920
 and of sound health,

950
00:45:13,920 --> 00:45:17,560
 so that we could actually build the relationship

951
00:45:17,560 --> 00:45:18,560
 that I wish we had?

952
00:45:21,360 --> 00:45:23,280
 So what I'm saying is when it comes to forgiveness,

953
00:45:23,280 --> 00:45:24,560
 don't be like me.

954
00:45:24,560 --> 00:45:27,800
 Don't wait.

955
00:45:27,800 --> 00:45:33,300
 'Cause then you don't know if you have the chance.

956
00:45:33,300 --> 00:45:37,340
 Why don't we all stand here today?

957
00:45:37,340 --> 00:45:49,520
 Maybe if you could just close your eyes.

